subsubsections.text_content:
AF: provides the packet description for 5GS treatment to PCF;
NEF/PCF/SMF/AMF: receives the packet description from AF, and then provides to the user plane node, i.e. UE/RAN/UPF;
UE/RAN/UPF:
-	Packet inspection/classification and labelling: according to the packet description from AF, labels (i.e. priority marker) the packet in the corresponding GTP-U header in UPF for downlink packets, PDCP header in UE for uplink packets; RAN maps the PDCP header and GTP-U header between UE and UPF for downlink and uplink packets.
-	Label handling: deals with the packet according to the label in the GTP-U/PDCP header, e.g. when it has to drop some packets in the QoS flow, the packet with the low priority label in the GTP-U/PDCP header will be dropped firstly.
